<H1>The Academic Academy</H1>
<P> Prerequisite(s):  Admission to the Academic Academy is made by the Program"s Coordinator. The Academy is a program designed for students as an alternative to the comprehensive high school. Students in grades 10 through 12 are served, as well as 9th grade students who have not yet completed the requisite coursework for admission to high school in Arlington Public Schools. This program is designed with small class settings, low teacher/student ratio, individualized teacher mentoring, and structured academics.</P>
